This paper deals with game theory and dynamical systems, which are both topics commonly found in the cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) sub-category. The use of better-response dynamics and the concept of rationality also suggest a connection to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also involves mathematical logic and set theory, which are relevant to the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-category. The use of convergence analysis and stability concepts suggest a connection to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with dynamical systems and control theory, which are relevant to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
